  "response": "Some common misconceptions between Marathi and Gujarati people include:\n\nMarathi Stereotypes about Gujaratis:\n1. Overly business-focused\n2. Extremely frugal/miserly\n3. Vegetarian by default\n4. Only interested in trading/commerce\n5. More westernized compared to Marathis\n\nGujarati Stereotypes about Marathis:\n1. More aggressive/quick-tempered\n2. Less business-oriented\n3. Traditional and conservative\n4. More focused on government jobs\n5. Strong regional pride\n\nThese are generalized perceptions and shouldn't be taken as factual representations of entire communities. Individual experiences vary greatly, and stereotypes often oversimplify complex cultural identities.",
